    "summary": "My passion and purpose is to help organizations to put their (human) capital not only to work for the organisational goals but deliver at the same time impact on the 17 UN Sustainable Development Goals.\n\nAs Global Director Corporate Responsibility at TNT I successfully delivered safe and low emission supply chain solutions to our customers as well as to people in need. Leading the unique Moving the World partnership with WfP was an excellent stepping stone to continue my mission for the humanitarian industry with CARE. It was great to use my businness + CSR knowledge and passion as a multiplier for CARE to save lives, defeat poverty and achieve social justice.    \n\nSustainability challenges including poverty, social unrest, climate change and environmental degradation have become ever more urgent. I have just started to help (part-time) the great team at the University of Tilburg to co-create their Science with a Soul Impact program. Hein Fleuren and myself are the co-founders of their Zero Hunger Lab. \n\n",
